main event: Several unidentified objects were detected on radar in Thompson, Iowa on July 1, 1957.
interesting points: The objects appeared in straight flight according to radar data., The sighting lasted between 10 to 15 minutes., It was classified as an unresolved sighting due to lack of complete evaluation., The observation was made during the day from 0900 to 0945., The report originates from Project 10073, likely related to Project Blue Book.
witness description: Radar detection, no confirmed visual witnesses
